---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Flooring Installation | Porcelain, Laminate, Vinyl & Hardwood in Venezuela"
  description="Professional flooring installation including porcelain tiles, laminate, vinyl SPC/PVC, and hardwood. Expert preparation and flawless finishes in Valencia, San Diego and Caracas."
  image="/images/suelo-porcelanato.webp"
  activePage="services"
>
  <header class="article-hero">
    <div class="hero-bg" style="background-image: url('/images/suelo-porcelanato.webp')"></div>
    <div class="hero-overlay"></div>
    <div class="hero-content">
      <a href="/en/services" class="back-link">← Back to Services</a>
      <span class="article-category">Essential Service</span>
      <h1 class="article-title"><span class="line">Flooring</span><span class="line gold">Installation</span></h1>
      <p class="article-excerpt">Professional flooring solutions that combine durability, comfort, and impeccable aesthetics.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="article-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="article-body">
        <p>The floor is the foundation upon which home comfort is built. A properly installed floor not only defines each room's aesthetics but provides thermal and acoustic insulation, facilitates cleaning, and withstands the passage of time and daily traffic. At ReformaT Venezuela, we master the installation of all modern flooring systems, adapting to the climate and each space's needs.</p>

        <p>We work with technical ceramics, high-density porcelain, high-resistance laminate floors, SPC/PVC vinyl, and natural or engineered wood. Each material requires specific substrate preparation, adhesive, or floating system techniques. Our team is trained to guarantee a flat, stable, and aesthetically impeccable finish.</p>

        <img src="/images/suelo-porcelanato.webp" alt="Professional flooring installation by ReformaT Venezuela" loading="eager" fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" />

        <h2>Types of Flooring We Install</h2>

        <h3>Ceramic & Porcelain Tiles</h3>

        <p>The most resistant and versatile option for warm, humid climates. Porcelain stands out for its low porosity, scratch resistance, and ability to imitate noble materials. Ideal for living rooms, kitchens, bathrooms, and high-traffic areas.</p>

        <p><strong>Advantages:</strong> Extreme durability, easy maintenance, moisture and temperature resistance, wide range of designs.</p>

        <h3>Laminate Flooring</h3>

        <p>Constructed with compacted layers featuring a high-resolution decorative layer and protective overlay. They offer the appearance of wood with greater impact resistance and simple maintenance.</p>

        <p><strong>Advantages:</strong> Fast installation (click system), economical, wear-resistant, compatible with radiant floor heating.</p>

        <h3>Vinyl Flooring (SPC/PVC)</h3>

        <p>The evolution of vinyl: stone plastic composite (SPC) or flexible vinyl (LVT) cores that are 100% water-resistant. Ideal for bathrooms, kitchens, basements, and commercial areas due to their total waterproofing and walking comfort.</p>

        <p><strong>Advantages:</strong> Waterproof, comfortable, quiet, installation over existing floors, great visual realism.</p>

        <h3>Natural & Engineered Hardwood</h3>

        <p>Wood provides warmth and timeless elegance. We work with solid wood (more sensitive to moisture) and engineered wood (more stable and recommended for the Venezuelan climate). Glued, nailed, or floating installation depending on the type.</p>

        <h2>The Technical Installation Process</h2>

        <p><strong>Phase 1: Substrate Evaluation:</strong> We measure the floor's residual moisture, verify flatness with a 6-foot straightedge, and detect possible irregularities. A moist or uneven substrate ruins any flooring.</p>

        <p><strong>Phase 2: Preparation & Leveling:</strong> We apply self-leveling compounds or repair mortars to correct unevenness. For floating floors, we install vapor barriers and high-density acoustic insulators.</p>

        <p><strong>Phase 3: Installation:</strong></p>

        <p><strong>Ceramic/Porcelain:</strong> Double gluing (floor and piece), use of leveling systems, uniform joints, and precise cutting with diamond blade.</p>

        <p><strong>Laminate/Vinyl/Wood:</strong> Floating system with perimeter spacers, clean cuts with table saw or professional knife, metal transitions at doorways.</p>

        <p><strong>Phase 4: Joints, Baseboards & Cleaning:</strong> We apply epoxy or cementitious grout, install matching baseboards (MDF, PVC, or aluminum), seal joints, and perform deep cleaning with specific machinery.</p>

        <p><strong>Phase 5: Delivery & Recommendations:</strong> Flatness verification, delivery of maintenance guide, and installation warranty. We advise you on cleaning products compatible with your new floor.</p>

        <h2>Common Flooring Challenges We Solve</h2>

        <p><strong>Uneven Substrates:</strong> Many Venezuelan properties have floors that aren't level. We use self-leveling compounds and repair mortars to create perfect bases.</p>

        <p><strong>Moisture Issues:</strong> Ground-floor properties often have moisture problems. We install proper vapor barriers and moisture-resistant materials.</p>

        <p><strong>Transition Areas:</strong> Professional transitions between different flooring materials and heights for safety and aesthetics.</p>

        <p><strong>Existing Floor Removal:</strong> Safe removal and disposal of old flooring materials before new installation.</p>

        <h2>Flooring Selection Guide</h2>

        <p>Choosing the right flooring depends on your specific needs:</p>

        <p><strong>High-Moisture Areas (Bathrooms, Kitchens):</strong> Porcelain, ceramic, or SPC vinyl are the best choices due to their water resistance.</p>

        <p><strong>Living Areas:</strong> Porcelain, laminate, or engineered wood provide durability with aesthetic appeal.</p>

        <p><strong>Bedrooms:</strong> Laminate, vinyl, or hardwood offer comfort and warmth underfoot.</p>

        <p><strong>Commercial Spaces:</strong> High-traffic porcelain or commercial-grade vinyl withstand heavy use while maintaining appearance.</p>

        <h2>Maintenance & Longevity</h2>

        <p>Proper maintenance extends your floor's life significantly:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Porcelain/Ceramic:</strong> Regular sweeping and occasional mopping with neutral pH cleaners</li>
          <li><strong>Laminate:</strong> Dry or damp mopping, avoid excessive water, use furniture pads</li>
          <li><strong>Vinyl:</strong> Easy cleaning with most household cleaners, highly stain-resistant</li>
          <li><strong>Hardwood:</strong> Regular dusting, occasional refinishing, protect from moisture and direct sunlight</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Why Choose ReformaT Venezuela?</h2>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Certified installers</strong> in ceramic and floating systems</li>
          <li><strong>Laser leveling:</strong> We guarantee flat surfaces without undulations</li>
          <li><strong>Premium fastening materials:</strong> Flexible adhesives and anti-stain grout</li>
          <li><strong>Technical advice:</strong> We indicate the ideal floor based on use, traffic, and humidity</li>
          <li><strong>Transparent quote:</strong> Includes preparation, material, labor, and cleaning</li>
          <li><strong>Installation warranty:</strong> We back every square meter installed</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Your Next Step</h2>

        <p>If you plan to change your home or business's flooring, avoid improvised installations that generate noise, unevenness, or detachment. Request a free technical visit to evaluate your space and receive a detailed quote.</p>

        <p><strong>Ready to renovate your floors?</strong> <a href="/en/contact">Schedule your free consultation</a> today.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="cta-wrapper">
      <h2 class="cta-title">Ready to Change Your Flooring?</h2>
      <p class="cta-text">Schedule a free consultation and receive a detailed no-obligation quote.</p>
      <a href="/en/contact" class="btn-premium btn-primary-premium">
        <span class="btn-content">Request a Quote</span>
        <span class="btn-border"></span>
        <span class="btn-shine"></span>
        <span class="btn-arrow">→</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .article-hero { position: relative; min-height: 80vh; display: flex; align-items: flex-end; justify-content: center; text-align: center; color: var(--white); overflow: hidden; padding-top: 140px; padding-bottom: 80px; }
  .hero-bg { position: absolute; inset: 0; background-size: cover; background-position: center; z-index: 1; }
  .hero-overlay { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(0,0,0,0.95) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,0.4) 60%, rgba(0,0,0,0.2) 100%); z-index: 2; }
  .hero-content { position: relative; z-index: 3; max-width: 900px; padding: 0 20px; }
  .article-category { display: inline-block; background: rgba(201,169,97,0.2); border: 1px solid var(--gold); color: var(--gold); padding: 8px 20px; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 2px; margin-bottom: 25px; backdrop-filter: blur(10px); }
  .article-title { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 5rem); font-weight: 400; margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 1.1; }
  .article-title .line { display: block; }
  .article-excerpt { font-size: 1.3rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: 400; }
  .back-link { display: inline-block; color: var(--gold); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 20px; transition: 0.3s; text-decoration: none; }
  .back-link:hover { color: var(--gold-light); }
  .article-section { padding: 80px 0; background: var(--white); }
  .article-body { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text); }
  .article-body h2 { font-size: 2.5rem; margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500; }
  .article-body h3 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem; color: var(--text); font-weight: 500; }
  .article-body p { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-weight: 400; }
  .article-body a { color: var(--gold); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gold); }
  .article-body ul, .article-body ol { margin: 1.5rem 0 1.5rem 2rem; }
  .article-body li { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-weight: 400; }
  .article-body img { border-radius: 12px; margin: 2.5rem 0; box-shadow: 0 15px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.08); width: 100%; }
  .article-body > p:first-of-type::first-letter { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 4.5rem; font-weight: 600; float: left; line-height: 0.75; margin-right: 0.15em; color: var(--gold); margin-top: 8px; }
  .cta-section { background: var(--bg); color: var(--white); text-align: center; padding: 110px 24px; width: 100%; }
  .cta-wrapper { max-width: 950px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; }
  .cta-title { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 3.6rem); font-weight: 400; margin-bottom: 24px; line-height: 1.15; color: var(--white); text-align: center; width: 100%; }
  .cta-text { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto 45px; font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.7; font-weight: 400; text-align: center; width: 100%; }
  .cta-section .btn-premium { padding: 20px 55px; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .article-hero { min-height: 70vh; padding-top: 120px; padding-bottom: 60px; }
    .article-title { font-size: clamp(2rem, 8vw, 3.5rem); }
    .article-excerpt { font-size: 1.15rem; }
    .article-body { font-size: 1.15rem; }
    .article-body h2 { font-size: 2rem; }
    .article-body h3 { font-size: 1.5rem; }
    .cta-section { padding: 90px 20px; }
    .cta-title { font-size: 2.2rem; }
    .cta-text { font-size: 1.15rem; }
  }
</style>